@startuml agent-payment-happy-path
title x402 Agent Payment — Happy Path

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam participantBorderColor #2196F3

actor "AI Agent" as Agent
participant "Developer Service\n(withPaywall middleware)" as Service
participant "PaymentSplitter\nContract (Arc)" as Contract
participant "Arc Network" as Arc

== Step 1: Initial Request ==
Agent -> Service : GET /api/data\n(no payment)

Service -> Agent : HTTP 402 Payment Required\nPAYMENT-REQUIRED: base64({\n  asset: "USDC",\n  network: "arc-mainnet",\n  amount: "10000",  // micro-USDC\n  payTo: "0xPaymentSplitter...",\n  developerId: "0xDev..."\n})

== Step 2: Agent Signs & Pays ==
Agent -> Agent : Decode payment requirements\nSign USDC authorization\n(via GatewayClient or own impl)

Agent -> Arc : Submit USDC tx\n→ PaymentSplitter contract\nwith (amount, developerId)

Arc -> Contract : Execute payment
Contract -> Contract : Verify amount >= required\nCheck nonce (replay protection)\nCredit developer balance\nDeduct platform fee

Contract -> Arc : Emit PaymentReceived event\n(txSig, developerId, amount, fee)

== Step 3: Retry with Payment ==
Agent -> Service : GET /api/data\nX-Payment: base64({\n  tx_sig: "0xABC...",\n  network: "arc-mainnet"\n})

== Step 4: Middleware Verifies ==
Service -> Arc : Verify tx_sig on Arc RPC\nCheck: tx exists in contract\nCheck: amount >= required\nCheck: developerId matches

Arc -> Service : ✅ Transaction confirmed

Service -> Agent : HTTP 200 OK\nPAYMENT-RESPONSE: base64({\n  success: true,\n  tx_sig: "0xABC...",\n  amount: "10000",\n  developer_credited: "9950"\n})\n\n{ ...resource data... }

== Step 5: Developer Withdraws (async) ==
note over Contract : Developer balance accumulates\nover many payments

"Developer" -> Contract : withdraw(amount)\n(any time)
Contract -> "Developer" : Transfer USDC to\nregistered wallet

@enduml
